## Description
The** Pweb HTTP ingress **resource&nbsp;allows to interact with a Pweb store through API and create a personalized URL (Purl) for a Pweb (see [Purl Generator API](https://code.doxee.com/confluence/display/DD/Doxee+Platform+3+Purl+Generator+API)).

## Additional creation parameters
None.

## Resource editor
None.

## Deploy parameters
![](data:image/png;base64,)

Section

Field

Description

**Configuration**

**Tenant**

Select the&nbsp;**Tenant** on which to deploy the resource from the drop-down menu.

**Store**

**Resource**

Select the **Pweb Store** resource that will be invoked when calling this endpoint.

> Important

If the selected store has not been deployed on the selected tenant, a warning message is displayed.

**Endpoint**

**Path**

Define the final part of the URL path to call.

> Note

The custom path may include "/" characters within (e.g. **custompath** or **custompath/subpath**)

For example: "/po-demo/2023-10";  the resulting URL will be: [*https://{prefix}-qa-aws-frnk-1-doxee-int.cloud.doxee.com*](https://da-qa-aws-frnk-1-doxee-int.cloud.doxee.com)*/****po-demo/2023-10****/process*

**Keys**

Select the [Ingress Credentials](/doxee-platform/docs/ingress-credentials-resource-reference) resource(s) to use for API authentication.

> Note

Up to 10 API keys can be used at the same time to avoid expiration issues.

**Parallel requests**

Select the maximum number of allowed requests per second. The available options are:

- 5&nbsp;*(default)*

- 10

- 15

- 20

- 25

- 30

- 40

- 50

- 60

- 70

- 80

- 90

- 100

- 120

- 140

- 160

- 180

- 200

> Important

If the selected rate limit doesn't include autoscaling, a warning message is displayed. In this case, it's necessary to adjust the capacity manually.

**Extraction**

**Duration (seconds)**

*(optional)* Enter a retention period (in seconds).

**Custom domain**

*(optional)* Enter a custom domain to use for the Purl.

> Tip

Click **Publish **to publish the release on the tenant.

Click **Deploy** to publish and enable the release on the tenant.
